          "SAMPLE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": {
                "nuclide": "42-MO-92",
                "field_identifier": "ENR",
                "value": 0.941
              },
              "free_text": [
                " Metallic, isotopically enriched",
                "Mo targets."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "DETECTOR": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "HPGE"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " HORUS detector array: 13 HPGe detectors (6 of",
                "them were equipped with BGO anti-Compton shields)",
                "mounted at five angles with respect to the beam axis.",
                "The detection efficiency was determined using",
                "standard sources and in-beam reactions, and by GEANT4",
                "simulation."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "METHOD": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "EXTB",
                "ACTIV",
                "GSPEC"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " The 92Mo(p,g)93Tc reaction was",
                "studied with in-beam gamma spectroscopy and",
                "activation. Total and partial cross sections were",
                "measured at seven proton energies between 3.7 and 5.3",
                "MeV. The beam energy was calibrated using the",
                "27Al(p,g)28Si resonance at Ep=3674.4 keV. The typical",
                "beam current amounted 50-350 nA, whereas the beam",
                "current was separately measured for the target, the",
                "target chamber and the Faraday-cup. A suppression",
                "voltage of -400V was applied on the target aperture.",
                "A thick gold backing (150 mg/cm**2) was mounted",
                "behind the 92Mo foils, which served as beam stop.",
                "Data from the detectors were recorded in list-mode",
                "format (energy, timing and veto information)."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "ADD-RES": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "COMP"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " The experimental results were compared to the",
                "data available from the literature, and to",
                "Hauser-Feshbach calculations using TALYS."
              ]
            }
          ],
